00:56:45,401 --> 00:56:48,613
-So you called us to nitpick over that?
-Nitpick? I'm your superior.

980
00:56:48,696 --> 00:56:50,240
Why would I do that with you two?

981
00:56:50,323 --> 00:56:51,950
If anything, I'd give you an order.

982
00:56:52,659 --> 00:56:55,161
All I'm saying is that
we've all done enough.

983
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:58,581
What do you mean by enough?
Are you telling us to give up?

984
00:56:58,665 --> 00:57:01,084
Hey, there is no giving up
when it comes to our cases.

985
00:57:02,377 --> 00:57:05,421
I'm saying there are many cases
we could solve with that time.

986
00:57:05,505 --> 00:57:06,673
Come on.

987
00:57:07,382 --> 00:57:09,467
We never just sat on our hands.

988
00:57:09,551 --> 00:57:12,512
The Behavioral Analysis Team
has done our duty by ourselves.

989
00:57:13,638 --> 00:57:16,349
What is it?
Stop beating around the bush and tell me.

990
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:17,559
Goodness.

991
00:57:18,476 --> 00:57:19,769
I'll be frank.

992
00:57:21,062 --> 00:57:23,148
Those up above aren't happy

993
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:26,025
with the Behavioral Analysis Team.

994
00:57:26,109 --> 00:57:28,278
They were never happy with us. Good grief.

995
00:57:28,903 --> 00:57:31,281
We're a workplace. An organization.
What can we do?

996
00:57:31,364 --> 00:57:33,199
Those men out there also are complaining

997
00:57:33,283 --> 00:57:36,286
about how your team is coming
in and out of the crime scenes.

998
00:57:36,369 --> 00:57:38,997
The only thing we can do
is investigate the crime scene.

999
00:57:39,914 --> 00:57:41,749
-If you stop us from doing that…
-I mean,

1000
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:44,252
I just want to stop by the crime scene
after the forensics are done.

1001
00:57:44,335 --> 00:57:45,420
What's the problem?

1002
00:57:45,503 --> 00:57:48,089
There are many other things
you can work on.

1003
00:57:48,173 --> 00:57:51,342
You know, those documents
you took from the cabinets.

1004
00:57:51,426 --> 00:57:54,512
You all study that and create data too.

1005
00:57:54,596 --> 00:57:57,849
That's our job, so we'll manage, okay?

1006
00:57:57,932 --> 00:58:00,018
Please don't stop us
from going to the crime scenes.

1007
00:58:00,101 --> 00:58:03,271
There's nothing he can do to stop us.
We can go whenever we want to.

1008
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:07,484
Forget it. I'm done with this. Goodbye.

1009
00:58:07,567 --> 00:58:09,903
We need to put an end to this.
Inspector Song.

1010
00:58:10,695 --> 00:58:13,323
I know you visit
the crime scene every day.

1011
00:58:14,365 --> 00:58:16,117
I'm not trying to stop you.

1012
00:58:16,201 --> 00:58:19,454
Please use your effort
on something else too.

1013
00:58:21,414 --> 00:58:22,499
Let's go.

1014
00:58:22,582 --> 00:58:24,751
I'm talking to him right now.

1015
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:27,587
It's my first time
having a serious talk with him.

1016
00:58:27,670 --> 00:58:30,423
You don't have to listen.
There's nothing serious about it.

1017
00:58:30,507 --> 00:58:31,382
Come on out.

1018
00:58:31,966 --> 00:58:33,092
That little…

1019
00:58:35,803 --> 00:58:36,971
Please excuse me.

1020
00:58:39,098 --> 00:58:40,934
You understand what I mean, right?

1021
00:58:47,357 --> 00:58:50,026
-What now?
-What do you mean?

1022
00:58:50,109 --> 00:58:52,278
I would've never started
if I was going to stop.

1023
00:58:53,321 --> 00:58:55,657
Do you know something we have in common?

1024
00:58:56,282 --> 00:58:58,368
-Nothing.
-Exactly.

1025
00:58:58,451 --> 00:59:00,119
Who do they think we are?

1026
00:59:00,203 --> 00:59:02,288
Let's not lose our spirit.
We have lots to do.

1027
00:59:05,792 --> 00:59:08,127
Mr. Gu Young-chun, please come on in.

1028
00:59:14,133 --> 00:59:15,843
X-RAY ROOM

1029
00:59:18,680 --> 00:59:21,766
Sir, we're about to take
an X-ray of your entire body.

1030
00:59:40,910 --> 00:59:42,996
64 DAYS SINCE THE OPEN SEARCH BEGAN

1031
00:59:43,079 --> 00:59:45,790
JANUARY 3, 2004

1032
00:59:50,920 --> 00:59:52,714
<i>Did he give up on committing
another crime to hide?</i>

1033
00:59:53,339 --> 00:59:54,382
<i>Or…</i>

1034
00:59:56,134 --> 00:59:58,511
<i>is he still planning another crime?</i>

1035
01:00:04,684 --> 01:00:06,227
You never miss a day.

1036
01:00:10,690 --> 01:00:13,151
We never know
when the crimes will start again.

1037
01:00:13,735 --> 01:00:14,777
Don't believe…

1038
01:00:16,279 --> 01:00:18,656
that you decided to begin
the open search all by yourself.

1039
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:23,745
The Special Crime Squad isn't incompetent

1040
01:00:24,579 --> 01:00:26,289
to the point we'd blindly follow

1041
01:00:26,372 --> 01:00:27,832
a rash decision.

1042
01:00:30,418 --> 01:00:31,586
From the outside,

1043
01:00:32,295 --> 01:00:35,298
it may seem like
the investigation is standing still.

1044
01:00:36,549 --> 01:00:39,093
Until the moment we catch the culprit,

1045
01:00:39,594 --> 01:00:41,429
even we sometimes feel that way.

1046
01:00:42,972 --> 01:00:44,098
However,

1047
01:00:45,642 --> 01:00:47,894
we came to this choice altogether.

1048
01:00:49,520 --> 01:00:52,857
What doesn't change is
how we came to the same decision.

1049
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:55,777
That all we want is to catch the culprit.

1050
01:00:57,987 --> 01:01:00,448
What's more important
than wanting to catch the culprit

1051
01:01:01,699 --> 01:01:04,077
is actually catching the culprit.

1052
01:01:07,830 --> 01:01:10,917
We will catch him. Certainly.

1053
01:01:13,252 --> 01:01:14,754
He will not stop.

1054
01:01:15,338 --> 01:01:16,881
We'll catch him before he goes on.

1055
01:01:21,052 --> 01:01:23,012
I thought it would work
once we stopped him.

1056
01:01:25,723 --> 01:01:27,809
I look through the daily reports
every morning,

1057
01:01:27,892 --> 01:01:30,436
and I don't see a report of a crime
in that same pattern.

1058
01:01:35,358 --> 01:01:36,442
What if…

1059
01:01:38,027 --> 01:01:39,904
What if the culprit changed the MO?

1060
01:01:42,824 --> 01:01:44,283
What do we do then?

1061
01:02:43,009 --> 01:02:45,303
DAILY CASE REPORT

1062
01:03:00,985 --> 01:03:02,653
JANUARY 30, 2004
VICTIM: KIM YANG-HEE

1063
01:03:02,737 --> 01:03:06,073
THE VICTIM WAS STABBED
WITH A CAMPING KNIFE

1064
01:03:45,154 --> 01:03:46,531
-Go home.
-See you later.

1065
01:03:46,614 --> 01:03:47,782
-Call me.
-Text me.

1066
01:03:47,865 --> 01:03:49,700
-Hurry. It's getting cold.
-Okay, bye.

1067
01:03:50,576 --> 01:03:52,537
-Call me.
-Okay, bye.

1068
01:03:53,120 --> 01:03:54,247
FEBRUARY 12, 2004

1069
01:03:54,330 --> 01:03:55,498
SINHEUNG 2-DONG, YEONGDEUNGPO-GU

1070
01:03:56,916 --> 01:03:58,000
<i>Are you home?</i>

1071
01:03:58,793 --> 01:04:00,211
<i>I'm almost home.</i>

1072
01:04:00,294 --> 01:04:02,046
TO SU-MIN

1073
01:05:26,714 --> 01:05:29,133
<i>The devil has yet again disappeared
without a trace.</i>

1074
01:05:29,216 --> 01:05:30,343
<i>Time is ticking.</i>

1075
01:05:30,426 --> 01:05:31,802
<i>If this becomes a cold case…</i>

1076
01:05:31,886 --> 01:05:35,056
Most murderers like him usually kill
for their own pleasure and enjoyment.

1077
01:05:35,139 --> 01:05:37,099
<i>It means killing makes them happy.</i>

1078
01:05:37,183 --> 01:05:39,435
<i>-Camping knife?
-Do you think it's the same guy?</i>

1079
01:05:39,518 --> 01:05:40,895
It's similar to the guy we're looking for.

1080
01:05:40,978 --> 01:05:43,022
<i>The murder weapon, MO, and time
don't match at all.</i>

1081
01:05:43,105 --> 01:05:44,815
<i>What if it's what we speculated?</i>

1082
01:05:44,899 --> 01:05:46,359
What if he failed to finish the job?

1083
01:05:46,442 --> 01:05:49,737
Then we have two serial killers
in this country.

